				 12 July, 2017,  18:12 | Author: Laverne Higgins			















 


 
 
 

Shareholders of record on Friday, September 1st will be paid a dividend of 1.82 per share by the aerospace company on Friday, September 22nd. As of December 31, 2016, approximately 83% of its products were sold under brands that it owned and the remainder of its products were sold for resale under customers' private labels, other brands or in bulk. Royal Bank Of Canada reiterated a "hold" rating and set a $263.00 price target on shares of Lockheed Martin Corporation in a research report on Tuesday, May 9th. The company has market cap of $298.41 million. 12,096 were reported by Eastern Bankshares. If the $313.84 price target is reached, the company will be worth $7.53 billion more. About 120 shares traded. Lockheed Martin Corporation has a 1-year low of $228.50 and a 1-year high of $287.75. It has underperformed by 2.51% the S&P500. About 2,350 shares traded. Dorman Products Inc. (DORM) has risen 57.51% since July 12, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 51.67% the S&P500.Analysts await Dorman Products Inc. After having $3.00 EPS previously, Lockheed Martin Corporation's analysts see 3.33 % EPS growth. The aerospace company reported $3.00 earnings per share for the quarter, beating the consensus estimate of $2.76 by $0.24.Since February 14, 2017, it had 0 insider buys, and 1 sale for $3.15 million activity. Comml Bank Of Ny Mellon Corp holds 0.01% in National Health Investors Inc (NYSE:NHI) or 317,857 shares. Summit Creek Advisors Llc owns 235,976 shares or 2.95% of their United States portfolio. Capital Investment Advisors holds 21,868 shares or 0.46% of its portfolio. The Virginia-based Shaker Financial Services Llc has invested 0.62% in the stock. The firm earned "Buy" rating on Wednesday, January 20 by Guggenheim. The rating was upgraded by Wolfe Research to "Outperform" on Wednesday, January 27.News coverage about Lockheed Martin Corporation (NYSE:LMT) has been trending somewhat negative on Saturday, Accern Sentiment Analysis reports. Therefore 59% are positive. Zacks upgraded the shares of NHI in report on Tuesday, September 22 to "Buy" rating. The rating was maintained by Stifel Nicolaus with "Buy" on Monday, November 9.
