Shares Trading unchanged at $290.81 (LMT) Lockheed Martin F-35s Surpass 100,000… 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsShares Trading unchanged at $290.81 (LMT) Lockheed Martin F-35s Surpass 100,000…
July 24, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



Lockheed Martin Corporation (NYSE:LMT):
Lockheed Martin F-35s Surpass 100,000 Flight Hours, System Development and Demonstration Completion On Track. 
 In the market the company is trading unchanged by 0.58% percent from yesterday’s close. 
 Lockheed Martin Corporation announced a dividend to be paid on Friday the 22nd of September 2017.  The dividend will be $1.820 per share for the quarter or $7.28 on an annualized basis.  This dividend represents a yeild of $2.52 which is the dividend as a percentage of the current share price.  The ex-dividend date is set for Tuesday the 30th of May 2017. 
 Lockheed Martin Corporation, launched on August 29, 1994, is a security and aerospace company. The Company is involved in the research, design, development, manufacture, integration and sustainment of technology systems, products and services. The Company operates through four segments: Aeronautics; Missiles and Fire Control (MFC); Rotary and Mission Systems (RMS), and Space Systems. The Company also provides a range of management, engineering, technical, scientific, logistics, system integration and cybersecurity services. Its main areas of focus are in defense, space, intelligence and homeland security. The Company serves both the United States and international customers with products and services that have defense, civil and commercial applications, with its principal customers being agencies of the United States Government..         Advertisement






 Shares last traded at $290.81 just a bit higher than the 50 day moving average which is $281.91 and a tad higher than the 200 day moving average of $270.01.  The 50 day moving average moved up $8.90 and the 200 day average moved up $20.80. 
 The P/E ratio is currently 16.87 and market cap is 83.75B.  As of the last earnings report the EPS was $17.28 and is projected to be $12.63 for the current year with 287,990,000 shares outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is estimated at $3.56 with next year’s EPS anticipated to be $14.12. 
 Investment firms have weighed in on the company recently.   On November 14 the stock rating was upgraded from “Hold” to “Equal-Weight” with a current price target of $275.00 in a report issued by Stifel Nicolaus. On November 10 the company was upgraded to “Equal-Weight” from “Underweight” and a price target of $275.00 was set in an announcement from Barclays.
 Equity analyst Barclays both upgraded the stock and raised the price target on November 10 changing the price target from $245.00 to $275.00 and moving the rating from “Underweight” to “Equal-Weight”. On November 9 the company was set at “Buy” according to a Deutsche Bank report which was a boost from the previous “Hold” rating.
 On October 6 analysts at  started covering the stock giving it an initial rating of “Outperform” and price target of $284.00. Equity analyst Baird added LMT to its research portfolio with an initial rating of “Outperform” and a price target of $284.00.
